# Theme Development Guide: Air-light

Based on the [Air-light documentation](https://github.com/digitoimistodude/air-light) and the theme structure, here is where you should place your code.

## 1. Where to place Styles (CSS/SASS)

Air-light uses a modern approach combining [theme.json](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/theme.json) for global settings and SASS for detailed styling.

### 🎨 Global Colors, Typography, and Spacing
Place these in [theme.json](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/theme.json).
- **Why**: This file is the "source of truth" for the WordPress Block Editor and automatically generates CSS variables (e.g., `--wp--preset--color--black`).
- **Example**: Update `settings.color.palette` to add new "Primary" or "Secondary" colors.

### 📐 SCSS Variables (Non-color)
Place technical variables (like breakpoints) in [assets/src/sass/variables/](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/assets/src/sass/variables/).

### 🧩 Components & Layouts
- **General Layout**: [assets/src/sass/layout/](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/assets/src/sass/layout/) (Header, Footer, Typography).
- **Reusable UI Components**: [assets/src/sass/components/](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/assets/src/sass/components/) (Buttons, Cards, etc.).
- **Page-specific Styles**: [assets/src/sass/views/](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/assets/src/sass/views/) (e.g., `front-page.scss`).

> [!TIP]
> After adding a new SCSS file, remember to `@use` it in [front-end.scss](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/assets/src/sass/front-end.scss).

---

## 2. Where to place HTML and PHP

### 📄 Main Page Templates
These are located in the **root directory** of the theme.
- [front-page.php](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/front-page.php): For the site's homepage.
- [page.php](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/page.php): For default static pages.
- [single.php](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/single.php): For single blog posts.

### 🧱 Modular HTML Fragments
Place reusable parts of your HTML in the [template-parts/](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/template-parts/) folder.
- **Example**: Create `template-parts/blocks/my-custom-hero.php` and include it using `get_template_part( 'template-parts/blocks/my-custom-hero' )`.

### ⚙️ Theme Logic, Actions, and Filters
Place functional PHP code in the [inc/](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/inc/) folder.
- [inc/hooks.php](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/inc/hooks.php): For general WordPress hooks.
- [inc/template-tags.php](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/inc/template-tags.php): For custom helper functions used in templates.

---

## Summary Table

| What to code | File / Directory |
| :--- | :--- |
| Primary Colors / Font Names | [theme.json](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/theme.json) |
| Navigation / Header Styles | `assets/src/sass/navigation/` or `layout/` |
| Custom Hero Section HTML | `template-parts/blocks/` |
| Custom Hero Section CSS | `assets/src/sass/components/` |
| Homepage PHP logic | [front-page.php](file:///c:/wamp64/www/spa/wp-content/themes/air-light/front-page.php) |
